      In each of the following scenarios with given events <m>A</m> and <m>B</m>, alculate <m>\Pr(A), \Pr(B)</m>, <m>\Pr(A\cap B)</m>, <m>\Pr(A \mid B)</m>, and <m>\Pr(B \mid A)</m>.
