        A continuous random variable <m>X</m> taking values in <m>[1, 2]</m> has p.d.f.
        <m>\displaystyle{f(x) = \frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{1}{x^2} + x\right)}</m>.
        Find the c.d.f.
        <m>F(x)</m>.
        Use your c.d.f.
        to find <m>\Pr\left(1 \leq X \leq \frac{3}{2}\right)</m>.
      </p>
